<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-02-0232 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Environmental Law Section of the 56th German Law Congress (DeutscherJuristentag) in Berlin dealt with the question whether it is necessaryto extend the individual protection against environmental pollution inthe field of civil and public law. A complete rewriting of the presentEnvironmental Law is rejected, but the individual rights should be extendedaccording to the different requirements.</TEXT></DOC>